    • fetchTable

      public static DefaultTableModel fetchTable(Connection connection, String query, String[] columnNames, String[] columnNamesUI)
      Fetches a table from the database using the provided query and column names. The column names are used to create the table model, and the data is populated from the database.
      Parameters:
      connection - Database Connection
      query - Query for database
      columnNames - Column names for table
      columnNamesUI - Column names for UI
      Returns:
      JTable containing the fetched data

    • CreateTableView

      public static JButton[] CreateTableView(DefaultTableModel table, String[] buttons, JPanel jPanel, JTable jTable)
      Creates a table view with the specified title and buttons. The table is added to the center of the frame, and buttons are added below the table. The buttons are returned as an array so the action listeners can be set.
      Parameters:
      table - Actual Table
      buttons - The Buttons
      jPanel - The Panel
      jTable - The displayed Table
      Returns:
      JButton array containing the buttons

    • AddButtonActionListener

      public static void AddButtonActionListener(JButton addButton, JTable jTable, DefaultTableModel table, Object[] defaultRowData)
      Action listener for the add button. Works for any table inserting a default set of data that is passed in. This function assumes the first column is always the ID which must be dynamically set inside the function unlike the rest of the row data.
      Parameters:
      addButton - The button that was pressed
      jTable - The displayed table
      table - The table to add to
      defaultRowData -

    • QueryButtonActionListener

      public static void QueryButtonActionListener(JButton button, JTable jTable, DefaultTableModel table, Connection connection, String query, String inputDialog, String[] columnNames, int paramCount)
      Action listener for the query button. Executes a SQL query and populates the table with the results. Use this function if the query only has one prompt.
      Parameters:
      button - The button that was pressed
      jTable - The displayed table
      table - The table to add to
      connection - The database connection
      query - The query to execute
      inputDialog - The input dialog
      columnNames - The column names for the table
      paramCount - The number of instances of the input in the query

    • QueryButtonTwoPromptsActionListener

      Action listener for the query button. Executes a SQL query and populates the table with the results. Use this function if the query only has two prompt.
      Parameters:

      jTable - The displayed table

    • DeleteButtonActionListener

      public static void DeleteButtonActionListener(JButton deleteButton, JTable jTable, DefaultTableModel table, JPanel jPanel)
      Action listener for the delete button. Deletes the selected row from the table. If no row is selected, a message dialog is shown to inform the user.
      Parameters:
      deleteButton - The button that was pressed
      jTable - The displayed table
      table - The table to add to
      jPanel - The panel

    • EditCellListener

      public static void EditCellListener(JTable jTable, JPanel jPanel, Object[] defaultRowData)
      Action listener for editing cell. It doesn't allow a cell to be left empty, if it is empty it reverts to the default value.
      Parameters:
      jTable - The displayed table
      jPanel - The panel
      defaultRowData - The default row data

    • ApplyTableChangesActionListener
